OL,3,CCurve head of finance jailed for
OL,4,Cstealing 'breath-taking' sum from
OL,5,Ctheatre
OL,7,FShe said: "That, perhaps, was folly.
OL,8,FShe was believing a win could change
OL,9,Ftheir fortunes."
OL,11,FShe added: "This was no doubt a very
OL,12,Fforceful and gripping addiction that
OL,13,Ftook over a woman who, up until her
OL,14,Fmid-40s, had been competent.
OL,16,F"All of that blown away by a clear,
OL,17,Fstrong addiction to gambling."
OL,19,FShe claimed her client had been
OL,20,Fshocked when Leicestershire Police
OL,21,Ftold her the full sum of the fraud.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G13/18
